@layout('livewire/layout')

<div class="page-hero">
  <div class="page-tag">Features</div>
  <h1>Validation</h1>
  <p class="page-lead">
    Livewire-style validation in Nimbus: return validation errors from actions, run real-time validation on <code>wire:model.live</code>, and access errors from JavaScript via <code>$wire.$errors</code>.
  </p>
</div>

<h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>
<p>
  Nimbus Livewire is Go-first, so there is no <code>$this-&gt;validate()</code> method like Laravel.
  Instead, validation integrates at two layers:
</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Action validation</strong>: return validation errors from <code>Call()</code> to trigger a 422 response and show messages in the UI.</li>
  <li><strong>Real-time validation</strong>: opt into auto-validation during <code>__sync</code> updates (triggered by <code>wire:model.live</code>).</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="basic">Basic validation (on submit)</h2>
<p>
  Return <code>livewire.FieldErrors</code> (first error per field) from your action:
</p>
<pre class="code-block"><code>func (c *CreatePost) Call(action string, params map[string]any) error {
  if action != "save" { return nil }

  st := c.State()
  title, _ := st["title"].(string)
  content, _ := st["content"].(string)

  errs := livewire.FieldErrors{}
  if strings.TrimSpace(title) == "" { errs["title"] = "required" }
  if len(strings.TrimSpace(content)) &lt; 3 { errs["content"] = "min:3" }
  if len(errs) &gt; 0 { return errs }

  // persist...
  return nil
}</code></pre>

<p>In your template, render per-field errors using <code>wire:error</code>:</p>
<pre class="code-block"><code>&lt;form wire:submit="save"&gt;
  &lt;input wire:model="title" /&gt;
  &lt;div wire:error="title"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;textarea wire:model="content"&gt;&lt;/textarea&gt;
  &lt;div wire:error="content"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/form&gt;</code></pre>

<h2 id="realtime">Real-time validation (wire:model.live)</h2>
<p>
  Implement <code>livewire.ValidationRulesProvider</code> and opt in to <code>ValidationOnUpdate()</code>.
  When the client runs <code>__sync</code> for a <code>wire:model.live</code> field, Nimbus validates only the changed field(s)
  and returns a 422 response with an error bag (best-effort Livewire parity).
</p>
<pre class="code-block"><code>func (c *CreatePost) ValidationRules() map[string]string {
  return map[string]string{
    "title": "required|min:3",
    "content": "required|min:3",
  }
}

func (c *CreatePost) ValidationOnUpdate() bool { return true }</code></pre>

<h2 id="js">Accessing errors in JavaScript</h2>
<p>
  The runtime stores the full error bag client-side and exposes it as <code>$wire.$errors</code>:
</p>
<pre class="code-block"><code>&lt;div x-data&gt;
  &lt;div x-show="$wire.$errors.has('email')"&gt;
    &lt;span x-text="$wire.$errors.first('email')"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>
<p>
  You can also use Nimbus directives:
</p>
<pre class="code-block"><code>&lt;div wire:show="$errors.has('email')"&gt;
  &lt;span wire:text="$errors.first('email')"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>

<h2 id="notes">Notes / limitations</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Rule support</strong>: Nimbus currently supports a small Laravel-like subset: <code>required</code>, <code>min:n</code>, <code>max:n</code>, <code>email</code> (more can be added).</li>
  <li><strong>Nested keys</strong>: rules are currently top-level keys only (no <code>todos.*</code> expansion yet).</li>
  <li><strong>Message localization</strong>: not implemented; rule messages are simple English strings.</li>
</ul>

